text.tspan: * Removing a node with a single child amounts to simply reassigning
that child's parent to be the node's parent
* If I want to remove a node that has two children
1. Find the node in the left subtree with the greatest value
2. Swap this value with the value to be removed
3. Remove the key that we want to remove. We're guaranteed
that this has at most one child in its reassigned position, so we
can use the previous two cases we established
